


✅ Correct Way to Set Up Pure-FTPd with User/Password
1. Run the container
docker run -d `
  --name pure-ftp `
  -p 21:21 -p 30000-30009:30000-30009 `
  -v C:\ftp\data:/home/ftpusers/myuser `
  -e PUBLICHOST=192.168.2.7 `
  stilliard/pure-ftpd:hardened

2. Create FTP User inside container

Now exec into the container and add a virtual user:

docker exec -it pure-ftp pure-pw useradd myuser -u ftpuser -d /home/ftpusers/myuser


It will ask for a password (set mypassword).

Then build the Pure-FTPd database:

docker exec -it pure-ftp pure-pw mkdb


Restart the container:

docker restart pure-ftp

3. Connect

Now in FileZilla / Explorer:

Host: 192.168.2.7

Username: myuser

Password: mypassword

Port: 21

⚡ Why your command failed

The -e FTP_USER_NAME and -e FTP_USER_PASS method doesn’t work with this hardened Pure-FTPd image.

You must use the pure-pw tool inside the container to create accounts.


